---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { t } from "../../i18n/ui";

const lang = "en";
---

<Layout
    title={t(lang, "nav.datenschutz")}
    lang="en"
    description="Privacy Policy of Jannik Menzel: Information about the handling of personal data on this website."
    keywords="Privacy, Privacy Policy, Jannik Menzel, Data, GDPR, Website"
    og={{
        title: `${t(lang, "nav.datenschutz")} – Jannik Menzel`,
        description:
            "Privacy Policy of Jannik Menzel: Information about the handling of personal data on this website.",
        url: "https://jannikmenzel.me/en/datenschutz/",
        image: "https://jannikmenzel.me/social-preview.png",
    }}
    twitter={{
        title: "Privacy Policy – Jannik Menzel",
        description: "Privacy policy of the website of Jannik Menzel.",
        image: "https://jannikmenzel.me/social-preview.png",
    }}
    canonical="https://jannikmenzel.me/en/datenschutz/"
>
    <main class="w-full container px-4 sm:px-16 mb-22" style="max-width: 1100px;">
        <!-- Header -->
        <header class="pt-20">
            <h1 class="text-center text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold font-display mb-4">
                {t(lang, "nav.datenschutz")}
            </h1>
            <div class="h-1 w-24 bg-primary mx-auto"></div>
        </header>

        <!-- Content -->
        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6 pt-22">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2 flex justify-between items-baseline">
                <span>Introduction</span>
                <span class="text-base font-thin">Status: June 5, 2026</span>
            </h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                This privacy policy informs you about the type, scope and purpose of the processing
                of personal data (hereinafter "data") within my online offer and the associated
                websites, functions and content as well as external online presences, such as my
                social media profile. It equally applies to data processing in the context of my
                freelance work as a web developer.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">Privacy at a Glance</h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                Here you will find a brief overview of what happens to your personal data when you
                visit this website or commission me as a freelancer. Personal data is any data that
                can be used to personally identify you.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">Who is responsible?</h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                The data processing on this website as well as in the context of my freelance work
                is carried out by me as the operator. You can find the contact details in the
                imprint.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">How is data collected?</h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                On the one hand, your data is collected by you providing it to me (e.g., via the
                contact form or by email). Other data is collected automatically by the hosting
                provider when you visit the website (e.g., technical data such as browser, operating
                system, time of page request). In the context of freelance projects, I process
                additional data (e.g., contract and billing data).
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">What is the data used for?</h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                Part of the data is collected to ensure the website functions without errors. Other
                data is used to process contact inquiries, to carry out and fulfill contracts, and
                to comply with legal obligations.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">Purpose of Processing</h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                Processing is carried out to answer contact inquiries, to conduct pre-contractual
                measures, to fulfill and execute contracts, to provide my content, and to safeguard
                legitimate interests (e.g., security and operation of the website, invoicing,
                compliance with tax retention obligations).
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">Contact Form</h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                If you contact me via the contact form, the data you enter (e.g., name, email
                address, subject, message) will be processed for the purpose of handling your
                request and for possible follow-up questions. Processing is based on your consent
                for general inquiries (Art. 6 Para. 1 lit. a GDPR) and on contract negotiation or
                performance for inquiries related to placing an order or an existing contractual
                relationship (Art. 6 Para. 1 lit. b GDPR).
            </p>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify mt-4" style="hyphens: auto;">
                The form is processed through the service <strong>Web3Forms</strong>
                (<a
                    href="https://web3forms.com"
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    class="underline">web3forms.com</a
                >). Your data is transmitted via HTTPS to Web3Forms and then forwarded to me via
                email. No form data is stored on my web server. For more information on how
                Web3Forms handles data, please refer to their
                <a
                    href="https://web3forms.com/privacy"
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    class="underline">Privacy Policy</a
                >.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">Customer Data and Freelance Work</h2>

            <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-medium mb-2 mt-6">
                Type and Scope of Data Processed
            </h3>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                In the context of my freelance work as a web developer, I process personal data of
                clients, prospects and business contacts. This includes in particular:
            </p>
            <ul class="font-thin text-justify list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1" style="hyphens: auto;">
                <li>
                    <strong>Contact data:</strong> Name, first name, company name, address, email address,
                    phone number
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Contract data:</strong> Quotes, order confirmations, project descriptions,
                    scope of services
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Payment and billing data:</strong> Bank details, billing address, payment
                    history
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Communication data:</strong> Email threads, project correspondence, feedback
                    and approvals
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Technical access data:</strong> Access credentials for systems required for
                    project execution (e.g., hosting, CMS), insofar as provided by the client
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-medium mb-2 mt-6">Purpose and Legal Basis</h3>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                This data is processed exclusively for the following purposes:
            </p>
            <ul class="font-thin text-justify list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1" style="hyphens: auto;">
                <li>
                    Performance of pre-contractual measures (quote preparation, project planning)
                    pursuant to Art. 6 Para. 1 lit. b GDPR
                </li>
                <li>
                    Fulfillment and execution of contracts (contract performance) pursuant to Art. 6
                    Para. 1 lit. b GDPR
                </li>
                <li>Invoicing and accounting pursuant to Art. 6 Para. 1 lit. b and c GDPR</li>
                <li>
                    Compliance with statutory retention obligations pursuant to Art. 6 Para. 1 lit.
                    c GDPR
                </li>
                <li>
                    Safeguarding legitimate interests (e.g., asserting or defending legal claims)
                    pursuant to Art. 6 Para. 1 lit. f GDPR
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-medium mb-2 mt-6">Storage Period</h3>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                Customer data is stored for the duration of the business relationship and thereafter
                for as long as statutory retention periods apply. Invoice and accounting records are
                generally retained for 10 years. Purely communication data without contractual
                reference is deleted as soon as it is no longer required for the respective purpose,
                at the latest after 3 years.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-medium mb-2 mt-6">Sharing of Customer Data</h3>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                Personal data of clients is only shared with third parties insofar as this is
                necessary for contract performance (e.g., passing on access data to hosting
                providers on behalf of the client), I am legally obligated to do so, or you have
                expressly consented.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">
                Hosting, Server Logs and Technical Data
            </h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                This website is hosted via <strong>GitHub Pages</strong> (a service of GitHub Inc., 88
                Colin P. Kelly Jr. St., San Francisco, CA 94107, USA). Each time the website is accessed,
                data is automatically collected in server log files, e.g., IP address, time of server
                request, referrer URL, browser used, and possibly accessed pages. This data is technically
                required to ensure stability and security of the page. The use of GitHub Pages results
                in a transfer of data to the USA. GitHub Inc. is certified under the EU-US Data Privacy
                Framework (DPF), so an adequacy decision pursuant to Art. 45 GDPR applies to the data
                transfer. For more information, please refer to
                <a
                    href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement"
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    class="underline">GitHub's Privacy Policy</a
                >.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">Analysis and Tracking Tools</h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                No analysis or tracking tools such as Google Analytics are used on this website.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">Your Rights</h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                You have the following rights with regard to the personal data concerning you: right
                of access, rectification, erasure, restriction of processing, data portability,
                objection to processing, withdrawal of consent, and the right to lodge a complaint
                with a data protection supervisory authority.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">Security</h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                I use technical and organizational security measures to protect your data against
                manipulation, loss, destruction, or unauthorized access by third parties.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-6 sm:mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-medium mb-2">Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p class="font-thin text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                I reserve the right to adapt this privacy policy if necessary. The current version
                will be published on this page.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-lightOff">
            <p class="text-justify" style="hyphens: auto;">
                For privacy-related questions, please use the contact form on the website or write
                an email to the address provided in the imprint.
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>
